This is the source code for the OWIDSlider gadget
as used on Wikipedia and MDWiki.

For more information see https://mdwiki.org/wiki/WikiProjectMed:OWID

The software is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike License.

It also includes jquery.mousewheel by Brandon Aaron which is MIT licensed.

If you want to test locally, open up demo.html in a web browser

== Installation instructions==

This assumes you have a MediaWiki installation with the gadgets extension installed.

* Create pages MediaWiki:Gadget-owidslider.js and MediaWiki:Gadget-owidslider.css copied from this repo
* Add `owidslider [ResourceLoader|default|categories=Pages using gadget owidslider]|owidslider.js|owidslider.css` to MediaWiki:Gadgets-definition
* Copy Template:Owidslider, Module:Owidslider from mdwiki
== Configuration Options ==

The OWIDSlider supports the following configuration options:

* `start` - The year to start displaying (default: most recent year)
* `mostRecent` - When set to true, always displays the most recent year of data available (default: false)
* `loop` - Whether to loop the animation (default: false)
* `startingView` - The initial view to display (e.g., "World")

To use the `mostRecent` option, add `"mostRecent": true` to the configuration JSON.
